tailliert nach. In der kurzen Zeit ihres Bestehens - regional unterschiedlich zwischen drei und zwölf Monate - fielen der deutschen Miliz in Polen nachweislich einige Tausend Menschen zum Opfer.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a FA license: uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/free-access-policy uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aGermanszPolandxHistoryy20th century. 0aGermans. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xAtrocities. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945zPoland. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh1 aWeckbecker, Arno, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA History 2000 - 2014z9783110635836oZDB-23-GHI40uhttps://doi.org/10.1524/9783486703177zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783486703177zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783486703177/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GHIc2000d2014  aZDB-23-GOA